I'll start by executing the network_fetcher tool to retrieve data from the API endpoint as the first step in the workflow.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            I'll execute the data_processing_validator tool next to validate the data we fetched. Since we need a schema for validation, I'll use a default schema.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {},
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Since the validator requires XML format input but we have JSON data from the network_fetcher, I'll first execute a data processing parser to convert the data to the required format.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {
    "input_format": "json",
    "output_format": "xml"
  }
}
</tool_call>

            I'll try executing the data_processing_transformer tool to convert the JSON data to XML format before validation, as this seems more appropriate for format conversion.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "xml",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Now that we have the data in XML format, I'll retry executing the data_processing_validator with the transformed data.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {},
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

                        Since the validation is failing, I'll try an alternative approach by first executing the data_processing_parser to ensure the data is properly structured before validation.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.xml",
  "options": {
    "input_format": "xml"
  }
}
</tool_call>

                        Now that the data is properly parsed, I'll make one final attempt to validate it using the data_processing_validator with the parsed XML data.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {},
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
